To solve this, we first condense the bases by factorising them, so.
\begin{align*}36 &= 6\times 6\\6^{19}&= 6^{10}\times 6^{9}\end{align*}
This allows us to directly simplify the expression by cancelling like terms.
\begin{align*}\frac{36^{10}}{6^{19}} &= \frac{(6\times 6)^{10}}{6^{19}}\\&= \frac{6^{10}\times 6^{10}}{6^{10}\times 6^{9}}\end{align*}
Canceling like terms leaves us with $\boxed{\frac{6^{10}}{6^9}}$.</think>
<answer>Since $\frac{6^{10}}{6^9} = 6$, the answer is 6.</answer>

